# 🕷️ Products Scrapers Collection

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.8%2B-blue?style=flat&logo=python)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-green)
![Maintenance](https://img.shields.io/badge/Maintenance-Active-brightgreen)

## 📖 Overview

**Products Scrapers** is a centralized repository containing a collection of Python scripts designed to extract product data from various e-commerce platforms and websites. 

I have consolidated these tools into a single location to demonstrate different scraping techniques, ranging from static HTML parsing to handling dynamic JavaScript-rendered content. These scripts are designed to fetch data points such as prices, product descriptions, images, reviews, and stock availability.

> **⚠️ Disclaimer:** This repository is for **educational purposes only**. Web scraping may violate the Terms of Service (ToS) of some websites. Please respect `robots.txt` files and use these tools responsibly.

---

## 📂 Repository Structure

The repository is organized by target website to keep the codebase modular and clean.

```text
Products-scrapers/
├── 📁 amazon/            # Scraper specific to Amazon (ASIN, Pricing)
├── 📁 ebay/              # Scraper for eBay listings
├── 📁 aliexpress/        # Scraper for AliExpress (Dynamic content)
├── 📁 utils/             # Shared utilities (User-Agent rotation, Proxy handling)
├── 📄 requirements.txt   # Global dependencies
└── 📄 README.md          # Project documentation
